SIMPLE: heterogamy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heterogamy
<hw>Het`er*og"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Heterogamous</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The process of fertilization in
plants by an indirect or circuitous method; -- opposed to
<xex>orthogamy</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>That form of alternate generation
in which two kinds of sexual generation, or a sexual and a
parthenogenetic generation, alternate; -- in distinction from
<contr>metagenesis</contr>, where sexual and asexual generations
alternate.</def> <rj><au>Claus & Sedgwick.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heterogangliate</ent>⟦br⟧
